                  </persName>
               
            , late of <placeName id="t17841208-194-defloc862">St. Paul's, Covent Garden</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17841208-194-defloc862" type="placeName" value="St. Paul's, Covent Garden"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17841208-194-defloc862" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17841208-194-defend1716 t17841208-194-defloc862"></join>, in the County of Middlesex, <rs id="t17841208-194-deflabel863" type="occupation">Esq</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17841208-194-defend1716 t17841208-194-deflabel863"></join>; was indicted for <rs id="t17841208-194-off864" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17841208-194-off864" type="offenceCategory" value="breakingPeace"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17841208-194-off864" type="offenceSubcategory" value="wounding"></interp>
               that he, being an evil disposed person, and of a wicked disposition, after the 1st of June, 1723, to wit on the <rs id="t17841208-194-cd865" type="crimeDate">21st of November</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17841208-194-off864 t17841208-194-cd865"></join> last, with force and arms, in the Parish aforesaid, with a certain pistol, loaded with gunpowder, and a leaden bullet, which pistol he then and there had and held in his right hand, unlawfully, wilfully, maliciously and feloniously, did shoot at one 
                     <persName id="t17841208-194-victim1717" type="victimName">
                        Huxley 
                        Sandon
                     <interp inst="t17841208-194-victim1717" type="surname" value="Sandon"></interp>
